### Version
2.6.11

### Reproduction link
[https://codesandbox.io/s/distracted-haze-f1r6e](https://codesandbox.io/s/distracted-haze-f1r6e)







### Steps to reproduce
Sometimes you use `inject` property to inject a method from parent or grand parents, but if you create a re-usable component it's better to add a default property to your injected key and you expect when the injection didn't resolve, the function in default key should be call instead of the main function which didn't resolve.

```js
new Vue({
  inject: {
    foo: {
      default: function() {
        return 1;
      }
    }
  },
  created() {
    this.foo();
  }
});
```

### What is expected?
I expect that default methods in inject get resolve without being called when it's resolving. it should return a function instead of calling them.

### What is actually happening?
I checked out the inject.js and I found that we are calling the default functions instead of returning them. this can cause issues.

